        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-09-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-09-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="249" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.50 Recovery/9–2449</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by Mr. G. Hayden Raynor of the
                        United States Delegation at the United Nations</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-09-24">September 24,
                            1949</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Participants:</cell>
                        <cell>M. Maurice Couve de Murville, French Delegation</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Mr. G. Hayden Raynor, U.S. Delegation</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p>During the course of Mr. Cohen’s<note n="1" xml:id="d249fn1">Benjamin V. Cohen,
                        an Alternate U.S. Representative at the United Nations.</note> and my
                    conversation with Couve on the Greek matter, I inquired casually of Couve if
                    there had been any recent developments in Western Europe with respect to the
                    idea of Spaak heading up the <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss>
                    Organization.</p>
                <p>Couve replied in almost these words: “What is the use of this now? Why should his
                    talents be wasted on this Organization now? The <gloss target="#t_OEEC1">OEEC</gloss> is dead. You have killed it by your tri-partite financial
                    talks in Washington.”<note n="2" xml:id="d249fn2">For documentation on these
                        talks, see <ref target="#pg_832">pp. 832</ref> ff.</note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
